HEADWORD: Gemini
<hw>Gem"i*ni</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[L., twins,
pl. of <ets>geminus</ets>; cf. Skr. <ets>j<?/mi</ets> related as brother
or sister.]</ety> <fld>(Astron.)</fld> <def>A constellation of the
zodiac, containing the two bright stars <xex>Castor</xex> and
<xex>Pollux</xex>; also, the third sign of the zodiac, which the sun
enters about May 20th.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

